ind":"text","text":"[q. v.], (O, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of cloth"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of matting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"raised,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"attached,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon a piece of wood"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a mast"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a yard"},{"kind":"text","text":"];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is beaten upon by the wind"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tuSaf~iquhu","text_ar":"تُصَفِّقُهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~iyHu","text_ar":"الرِّيحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and causes the ship,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"boat, to go along:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, TA:) so called because it is raised ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yu$oraEu","text_ar":"يُشْرَعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yurofaEu","text_ar":"يُرْفَعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":") above the ship, or boat: (TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$oriEapN","text_ar":"اَشْرِعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uruEN","text_ar":"شُرُعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (O, K;) the former a pl. of pauc. (O.) ―         -b2-  And hence, as being likened thereto, (TA, [and the same is implied in the S and O,]) (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"neck"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a camel. (S, O, K, TA.) Sometimes they said of a camel,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafaEa $iraAEahu","text_ar":"رَفَعَ شِرَاعَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He raised his neck:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, TA.) ―         -b3-  One says also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN $iraAEu AlA^anofi","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ شِرَاعُ الاَنْفِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man having the nose extended,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"long."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$oraEu","text_ar":"اَشْرَعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b4-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iroEapN","text_ar":"شِرْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places."}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","O","Msb","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n22149","headword_ar":"شَرَّاعٌ","root":"$rE","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A seller of the flax called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ariyE","text_ar":"شَرِيع"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IAar, K.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}